; engine-strict is intentionally OFF (not true) — see design/ACTIONS.md P1
; "Dev-toolchain drift past Node 14". Dev-toolchain reconcile EXECUTED 2026-06-16:
; the top-level dev tools are now pinned to Node-14.15 versions (eslint 7.32.0,
; @nuxtjs/eslint-config 6.0.1, concurrently 7.6.0, cross-env 7.0.3, cssnano 4.1.11),
; and lint + 319 tests + `nuxt build` all pass on the pinned tree. Two TRANSITIVE
; over-declarers are now the ONLY Node-engine mismatches left in the installed tree:
; consola@3 (wants 14.18+) and node-releases (wants 18+). engine-strict=true would
; hard-fail the install on those two, so it stays false until they are pulled down
; via `overrides` (a small follow-up + one more install). Node 14.15 and all runtime
; deps stay locked.
; DO NOT flip to true until consola + node-releases are overridden (its own task).
engine-strict=false
